==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic.  Cognate with Middle Low German ''ōst'' (Dutch [[oest]] ‘knot, tree-stump’), Old High German [[ast]] (German [[Ast]] ‘branch’), Gothic [[𐌰𐍃𐍄𐍃]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /o:st/

===Noun===
'''ōst''' ''m''
# a [[knot]] in a tree

